From 337f00a0bc62d7cb7d10ec0b872c79009a1641df Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yang Yingliang <yangyingliang@huawei.com>
Date: Tue, 31 Aug 2021 16:42:36 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] usb: dwc2: check return value after calling platform_get_resource()
Git-commit: 856e6e8e0f9300befa87dde09edb578555c99a82
Patch-mainline: v5.15-rc3
References: stable-5.14.11 bsc#1225330 CVE-2021-47409

[ Upstream commit 856e6e8e0f9300befa87dde09edb578555c99a82 ]

It will cause null-ptr-deref if platform_get_resource() returns NULL,
we need check the return value.

Signed-off-by: Yang Yingliang <yangyingliang@huawei.com>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20210831084236.1359677-1-yangyingliang@huawei.com
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Sasha Levin <sashal@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/usb/dwc2/hcd.c | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/usb/dwc2/hcd.c b/drivers/usb/dwc2/hcd.c
index 2a7828971d05..a215ec9e172e 100644
--- a/drivers/usb/dwc2/hcd.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/dwc2/hcd.c
@@ -5191,6 +5191,10 @@ int dwc2_hcd_init(struct dwc2_hsotg *hsotg)
 	hcd->has_tt = 1;
 
 	res = platform_get_resource(pdev, IORESOURCE_MEM, 0);
+	if (!res) {
+		retval = -EINVAL;
+		goto error1;
+	}
 	hcd->rsrc_start = res->start;
 	hcd->rsrc_len = resource_size(res);
 
